dcterms:description: DEXTRON is a stochastic simulation environment that utilizes real human trajectories for training end-to-end grasping policies in human-in-the-loop robot systems.
dcterms:title: DEXTRON (DEXTerity enviRONment)

dcterms:description: Υ is a dataset of tuples that includes state, action, and final outcome of rolling out a policy in the environment, used for training a success model.
dcterms:title: Υ (dataset for training the success model)

dcterms:description: Gs is a database of successful policy-environment parameters collected during the Monte Carlo simulation.
dcterms:title: Gs (database of successful policy-environment parameters)

dcterms:description: This dataset is used for training the Behavior Cloning (BC) policy based on transitions from expert policies and environment settings.
dcterms:title: Dataset for training the BC policy

dcterms:description: ΥEX consists of transitions from rolling out sampled expert policies in the environment.
dcterms:title: ΥEX (transitions from rolling out sampled policy πe)

dcterms:description: ΥRL includes transitions from trained RL policy roll-outs in an environment setting sampled from Gs.
dcterms:title: ΥRL (transitions from trained RL policy roll-outs)
